
4. Datatypes for each column (short format):
- id – NUMBER(4), NOT NULL
- loc_name – VARCHAR2(20), NOT NULL
- date_opened – DATE, NOT NULL
- address – VARCHAR2(30), NOT NULL
- city – VARCHAR2(20), NOT NULL
- zip_postal – VARCHAR2(10), nullable
- phone – VARCHAR2(15), NOT NULL
- email – VARCHAR2(80), NOT NULL, UNIQUE
- manager_id – NUMBER(4), NOT NULL
- contact – VARCHAR2(40), nullable

5. Nullable columns:
- zip_postal
- contact

6. CREATE TABLE statement (column-level constraints):

CREATE TABLE global_locations (
    id NUMBER(4) CONSTRAINT pk_global_id PRIMARY KEY,
    loc_name VARCHAR2(20) NOT NULL,
    date_opened DATE NOT NULL,
    address VARCHAR2(30) NOT NULL,
    city VARCHAR2(20) NOT NULL,
    zip_postal VARCHAR2(10),
    phone VARCHAR2(15) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR2(80) CONSTRAINT uq_email UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    manager_id NUMBER(4) NOT NULL,
    contact VARCHAR2(40)
);

7. DESCRIBE table to view summary:
DESC global_locations;

8. CREATE TABLE statement with table-level UNIQUE constraint (do not execute):

CREATE TABLE global_locations (
    id NUMBER(4),
    loc_name VARCHAR2(20) NOT NULL,
    date_opened DATE NOT NULL,
    address VARCHAR2(30) NOT NULL,
    city VARCHAR2(20) NOT NULL,
    zip_postal VARCHAR2(10),
    phone VARCHAR2(15) NOT NULL,
    email VARCHAR2(80) NOT NULL,
    manager_id NUMBER(4) NOT NULL,
    contact VARCHAR2(40),
    CONSTRAINT pk_global_id PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT uq_email UNIQUE (email)
);
